		<title>ProcurePro Raises $11M for AI Construction Procurement</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/procurepro-raises-11m-for-ai-construction-procurement/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 10:21:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200950</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>ProcurePro has announced the closing of an $11 million funding round. The investment is targeted at accelerating ProcurePro&#8217;s push toward digitizing and automating the manual procurement processes built in the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/procurepro-raises-11m-for-ai-construction-procurement/" data-wpel-link="internal">ProcurePro Raises $11M for AI Construction Procurement</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://ventureburn.com/meatly-raises-10m-series-a-cultivated-meat/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">ProcurePro </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has announced the closing of an $11 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/meatly-raises-10m-series-a-cultivated-meat/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The investment is targeted at accelerating ProcurePro&#8217;s push toward digitizing and automating the manual procurement processes built in the traditional construction industry of a $13 trillion supply chain.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">QIC Ventures, the venture arm of one of Australia’s largest sovereign wealth funds, led the funding round. Investors involved in the round include existing investors such as Airtree and Glitch Capital, as well as Isai, the venture fund that manages the venture arm for global construction giant Bouygues. This Series B funding round pushes ProcurePro’s valuation to over $80 million.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Spreadsheet Problem&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For years, the construction industry has been one of the most under-digitised parts of the world. Tendering, the process of selecting and contracting subcontractors, labour equipment and supplies, often relied on ad hoc communication via multiple emails, paper copies, and unreliable spreadsheets. The result was often &#8220;margin erosion&#8221;, where unforeseen costs and delays would threaten the razor-thin profit margin of large projects.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200951" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200951" class="wp-image-200951" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ProcurePro_Logo.jpg" alt="ProcurePro Logo" width="400" height="82" /><p id="caption-attachment-200951" class="wp-caption-text">Source: ProcurePro</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The ProcurePro platform solves these problems by centralizing the entire process in an integrated &#8220;control centre&#8221;. Through digitally encapsulating the complete lifecycle of a trade package, from first scheduling and tendering all the way through to the final subcontract, the platform offers contractors visibility of project spend in real time. Contractors can thus proactively mitigate the financial risk and secure the desired project margin before contracts are even being finalized.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/meatly-raises-10m-series-a-cultivated-meat/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Meatly Raises £10.4M Series A To Scale Cultivated Meat Production</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Harnessing a Data Powerhouse</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The critical difference that this funding round makes, however, is ProcurePro&#8217;s move towards more advanced artificial intelligence. ProcurePro has been used in over 6,000 projects worldwide, accounting for more than $90B worth of construction, and has accumulated huge amounts of real procurement data, including pricing, supply chain and other performance trends.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new data site will now be applied to turn into predictive AI tools. Instead of &#8220;making it up&#8221; based on years of historical memory, construction companies will now be able to have ProcurePro&#8217;s AI tell them what a new project will cost based on years of validated, hyper-granular purchasing data, all in a matter of minutes! What previously took weeks of discussion in project planning meetings will now take minutes.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Global Footprint and Growth</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although originally launched in Brisbane, Australia, ProcurePro is quickly making itself known around the globe. The site is currently available in the United Kingdom, Ireland, and the Middle East. </span>Thanks to $11M in funding, the company is opening its first U.S. branch for North American markets. This expansion includes hiring around 100 employees globally over the next 24 months. New hires will join engineering, product, and go-to-market teams in London, Brisbane, Dubai, and the U.S. With rising material costs and labour shortages in construction, digital certainty has never been more critical.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/procurepro-raises-11m-for-ai-construction-procurement/" data-wpel-link="internal">ProcurePro Raises $11M for AI Construction Procurement</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
